  {
    "id": "2036192940947566842",
    "text": "- The post promotes a viral claim that Vice President JD Vance can assume the Senate Majority Leader role from John Thune without resigning, citing John Adams' 1790s Senate presidency as precedent, amid apparent GOP delays on key legislation.\n- This interpretation misapplies history: the Majority Leader position, formalized in 1925, is elected internally by majority party senators, and the VP's Senate role is ceremonial presiding, not leadership appointment, per Senate rules and constitutional scholars.\n- Replies reflect MAGA discontent with Thune as ineffective or RINO, with calls to act urgently, though a minority accurately debunk the claim, highlighting ongoing intra-party tensions in a slim Republican Senate majority.",
