    "id": "2036192203345699042",
    "text": "Tech Bois in the house, loving everything Vance and even hosting. Per Grok \n\nJoe Lonsdale set up and hosted the JD Vance fundraiser dinner in Austin tonight (March 23, 2026).\nHe's the co-founder of Palantir Technologies (that's the \"Palenter\" connection you're thinking of-likely a typo for Palantir), a major GOP donor, and a venture capitalist. Multiple reports confirm the event is taking place at his home in Austin, with high-tier pricing like $50,000 per person / $100,000 per couple for attendance, and up to $250,000 for host committee spots. It's framed as an RNC (Republican National Committee) fundraiser, with Vance as the headliner, but Lonsdale is the primary host organizing it locally.\nThis aligns with his long-standing support for Vance and broader ties in the tech-right circle (including past connections to Peter Thiel via Palantir). Recent coverage from outlets like Axios, the Austin American-Statesman, and posts on X (including leaked invitations) all point directly to him as the one who put it together at his place.\nIf you're referring to something beyond hosting-like who leaked the invite or coordinated broader logistics-it's not clear from public sources, but Lonsdale is the key figure behind this specific event.",
